@startuml
title Sequence Diagram: NeoVex Agentic Task Flow (e.g., Code Refactoring)
' Version: 0.1.0 — update this diagram whenever the task flow changes
' Reading guide: vertical lines = processes, horizontal arrows = calls/IPC, time flows downward
' Mental model: read this like strace output across multiple processes

actor User <<Implementer / Sovereign Reviewer — Principle 10>>
actor AISpecialist <<Designer / PR Submitter — no merge authority>>
participant Neovim
participant NvimPlugin <<mlua Lua/Rust FFI>>
participant RustServer <<axum localhost:7777>>
participant Gemini <<Primary Cloud LLM>>
participant Ollama <<Fallback — Last Resort Only>>

autonumber

User -> Neovim : Trigger :AgentRefactor (keybinding)
Neovim -> NvimPlugin : Invoke plugin logic via Lua/Rust FFI

alt Primary Path — Custom Rust Bridge (Principle 9)
  NvimPlugin -> RustServer : HTTP POST /refactor\n{code context, task description, file path}
  activate RustServer

  loop Agent Orchestration Loop (rig pipeline)
    RustServer -> Gemini : Delegate sub-task via agentai ToolCaller\n"Suggest refactor with safety and correctness checks"
    Gemini --> RustServer : Response (code delta, reasoning)
    RustServer -> RustServer : Validate via rig pipeline\nUpdate StateManager (Arc<Mutex<T>>)
  end

  alt Cloud quota available (normal case)
    RustServer --> NvimPlugin : Return processed result (JSON)
  else Cloud quota exhausted mid-task
    RustServer --> NvimPlugin : ⚠ QUOTA FLAG\nOption A: switch provider\nOption B: continue on Ollama (degraded)\nOption C: abort and preserve state
    NvimPlugin --> Neovim : Surface options to User
    User -> NvimPlugin : Select option
    opt User selects Ollama fallback
      RustServer -> Ollama : Re-route with quality-degradation warning
      Ollama --> RustServer : Degraded response
      RustServer --> NvimPlugin : Result + prominent degradation indicator
    end
  end

  deactivate RustServer

else Fallback Path — Existing Plugin (when rust_agent_server unavailable)
  NvimPlugin -> Neovim : Route to avante.nvim / opencode.nvim
  Neovim -> Gemini : Proxy API call via plugin auth
  Gemini --> Neovim : Response
  Neovim --> NvimPlugin : Forward result
end

NvimPlugin --> Neovim : Apply buffer edits
Neovim --> User : Display refactored code + routing indicator (model/provider/budget)

note over AISpecialist, RustServer
  Collaboration (Principle 10):
  AISpecialist designs new agent module logic in Antigravity,
  submits PR. User reviews Rust code, approves, merges.
  AISpecialist PR is a proposal — never a commit.
end note

AISpecialist -> RustServer : PR: new agent module (proposal only)
User -> RustServer : Code review in Antigravity
User -> RustServer : Approve and implement in Rust
User -> Neovim : Test integration end-to-end

@enduml
